divs: Sighting DetailsThe photos were shot shortly after I had returned to my hotel room in Strande, Germany, located just north of Kiel on the east coast of northern Germany. The direction was south, towards Kiel from Strande. The lights in all 3 photos were not visible with the naked eye and no sounds were heard. Two people were with me while I shot the photos, and neither one of them saw or heard anything. I noticed the lights after viewing the first frame, by looking at the LCD on the back of the camera (Nikon D40). This camera is IR sensitive, which made me think that maybe the camera had captured something not normally visible. The other possibility would be a reflection inside the lens of the camera. The pictures (shot in RAW file format, but sent as JPG): 0726 14 sec exposure 0728 10 sec exposure 0744 30 sec exposure I can send the original RAW files which contain all the EXIF information, but chose not to at this time, due to the large file size.
Summary: Casual long exposure photos of the city at night, reveal odd lights.
